description:
TITLE : cohn3, modular equations for special algebraic number fields

REFERENCES :

See the PoSSo test suite.

Andre' Galligo and Carlo Traverso:
"Practical Determination of the dimension of an algebraic variety",
in E. Kaltofen and S.M. Watt, Eds "Computers and Mathematics",
pages 46-52, 1989.

H. Cohn: "An explicit modular equation in two variables and
Hilbert's Twelfth problem", Math. of Comp. 38, pp. 227-236, 1982.

H. Cohn, J. Deutch: "An explit modular equation in two variables
for Q[sqrt(3)]", Math. of Comp. 50, pp. 557-568, 1988.

NOTE :

From the 213 solution paths, 110 converged to finite solutions.
There are eight highly singular solutons with zero components
that are probably not isolated.
